In my life, I have worn MANY hats & had MANY titles, so let me take a moment to RE-Introduce myself: 

Brittany Nicole. 
First of her name. 
From the House of Dorm, Beatty , & Hawkins. 
Aka: The Model. The Actress. The Singer. The Dancer. The Rapper. The Host. The Photographer. The Videographer. The Editor. The Soldier. The Veteran……. 

& now thanks to you guys: The Visionary ❤️

- THANK YOU GUYS SO MUCH! The love & support has been overwhelming. Thank you to my clients for believing in me & keeping me booked and busy! The voters who chose ME for “The Visionary” ❤️

The most recent issue of the Downtown York, PA magazine, jointly published with the York County Economic Alliance, is the Changemaker Edition. Individuals, like Brittany Dorm, utilize their talents and drive to make things happen in our community. 

"I came back to York City because it’s where I am from, it’s where my family is. My ties are here. York has always been the one that sustains me and keeps me doing what I love."

Brittany has positioned her business, Brittany Nicole Photography, L.L.C, to reflect her natural and learned skills to bring the personalities of her clients through in the photos. She is known for accurately capturing melanated skin tones that are true to the eye, representing these tones correctly through photography. 

Read more of Brittany's story here: https://issuu.com/downtownyorkpa/docs/winter22/s/17570294.

Learning I was not allergic shellfish was the greatest news I ever received, however, hearing I was in the Pre-Diabetic range at that same appointment quickly shifted things. The VA didn’t seem to think it was a big deal, but I did. So with some help from @injectorina & @remedyrose333, getting on natural products & taking my health serious, I had to start somewhere. 
Sometimes It’s hard to “feel” like you’re making progress as you see yourself everyday, but trust the process. Take those progress photos. You don’t have to run, just walk! But whatever you do, just START! 💖

What keeps me motivated?:
“You Got This” by @todrick shook me to my CORE & had me ugly crying the first time I heard it. For the next two months, “JIM” was the soundtrack to my life. 

Cycling on Apple Fitness with: @tyrelldesean 
I am obsessed with closing my rings & Ty’s classes are challenging yet fun. He has a 45min Disney ride that I love to frequently follow as Pixie Dust takes me where I need to be 😂 If you want to keep each other motivated and challenge your rings everyday, let’s add each other on the Fitness app!

November 1, 2022 || York, PA 👉🏾 Phoenix, AZ 

The look on people’s faces when I tell them I packed my car & moved across country 😂  Woke up at 3am and the next 4 days was me and the highway. Been an east coast girl all my life so I was sooo ready for warmer weather, I figured leaving before the holidays would beat winter. LIES! I ended up in a snow storm in New Mexico! Of all places! 😭 Well, I learned a lot about this country on this drive 😂

I know ya’ll think I’m crazy! I lived in New York, Pennsylvania, Maryland, & Georgia, but at the age of 30 I just wanted something DIFFERENT! Is Arizona the final chapter? Knowing me? Probably not! 😂 However, I’m so thankful for taking this leap of faith as it has truly been A YEAR! So here’s to any other Dreamer out there. If it sounds crazy? DO IT! If they tell you you’re insane: OWN IT!
